{"title_page": "John R. Bass", "text_new": "{{short description|American diplomat and ambassador}}\n{{other people|John Bass}}\n{{Infobox Ambassador\n|name         = John Bass\n|image        = John R. Bass official photo.jpg\n|office       = [[United States Ambassador to Afghanistan]]\n|president    = [[Donald Trump]]\n|term_start   = December 12, 2017\n|term_end     = January 6, 2020\n|predecessor  = [[Hugo Llorens]]\n|successor    = [[Ross Wilson (ambassador)|Ross Wilson]] (acting)\n|office1      = [[United States Ambassador to Turkey]]\n|president1   = [[Barack Obama]]<br />[[Donald Trump]]\n|term_start1  = October 20, 2014<ref name=\"Ambassador bio\">{{cite news|url=http://turkey.usembassy.gov/about-us/ambassador-john-bass.html|title=Ambassador Biography|publisher=Embassy of the United States Ankara, Turkey|accessdate=14 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129011614/http://turkey.usembassy.gov/about-us/ambassador-john-bass.html|archive-date=29 November 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|term_end1    = October 15, 2017<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://tr.usembassy.gov/embassy-consulates/ankara/former-ambassadors/ |title=Former Ambassadors |website=U.S. Embassy & Consulates in Turkey |language=en-US |access-date=2018-07-07}}</ref>\n|deputy1      = Philip Kosnett\n|predecessor1 = [[Francis J. Ricciardone Jr.]]\n|successor1   = [[David M. Satterfield]]\n|office2      = [[Executive Secretary of the Department of State]]\n|president2   = Barack Obama\n|term_start2  = October 8, 2012\n|term_end2    = July 18, 2014\n|predecessor2 = [[Stephen Mull]]\n|successor2   = [[Joseph Macmanus]]\n|office3      = [[United States Ambassador to Georgia]]\n|president3   = Barack Obama\n|term_start3  = October 16, 2009\n|term_end3    = July 17, 2012\n|predecessor3 = [[John F. Tefft]]\n|successor3   = [[Richard Norland]]\n|birth_date   = {{birth year and age|1964}}\n|birth_place  = [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n|death_date   =\n|death_place  =\n|spouse = Holly Holzer Bass<ref name=\"U.S. Ambassador to Turkey: Who Is John R. Bass?\" />\n|alma_mater   = [[Syracuse University]]\n}}\n'''John Rodney Bass II'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.congress.gov/nomination/100th-congress/962|title=PN962 \u2014 Foreign Service|date=April 27, 1988|website=U.S. Congress|accessdate=3 July 2018}}</ref> (born 1964) is an American diplomat, who served as the [[United States Ambassador to Afghanistan]] from 2017 to 2020. He was the [[United States Ambassador to Turkey|U.S. ambassador to Turkey]] 2014\u20132017 and the [[United States Ambassador to Georgia|U.S. ambassador to Georgia]] 2009\u20132012.\n\n==Career==\nBass is from [[upstate New York]].<ref name=\"Ambassador bio\"/> He graduated from [[Syracuse University]] in 1986 and was a newspaper editor and political campaign consultant before joining the Foreign Service in 1988. Shortly after, he was posted to Belgium, the Netherlands and Chad.<ref name=\"U.S. Ambassador to Turkey: Who Is John R. Bass?\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allgov.com/news/appointments-and-resignations/us-ambassador-to-turkey-who-is-john-r-bass-140810?news=853921|title=U.S. Ambassador to Turkey: Who Is John R. Bass?|publisher=ALLGOV|date=August 10, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 1998, he worked for Deputy Secretary of State [[Strobe Talbott]], first as a special assistant for Europe and Eurasia including as part of the peace negotiations in the [[Kosovo War]]. He was later named as Talbott\u2019s chief of staff in 2000, coordinating policy on arms reduction with Russia.<ref name=\"U.S. Ambassador to Turkey: Who Is John R. Bass?\"/>\n\nIn 2005, Bass was named director of the State Department Operations Center. He was sent to Iraq in 2008 as the leader of a provincial reconstruction team.<ref name=\"U.S. Ambassador to Turkey: Who Is John R. Bass?\"/> He speaks [[Italian language|Italian]] and [[French language|French]].<ref name=\"Ambassador bio\"/>\n\nIn October 2012, he was appointed [[Executive Secretary of the United States Department of State]] and served as the liaison between the State Department's many bureaus and the leadership offices of the [[Secretary of State|Secretary]], the Deputy Secretaries, and the [[Director of Policy Planning]].\n\nIn October 2017, after the U.S. decided to suspend non-immigrant visa services within Turkey, Turkish President [[Recep Tayyip Erdo\u011fan]] said the Turkish government would no longer recognize Bass's authority as a U.S. ambassador. The cancellation of visitor visas came after a Turkish court ordered the arrest of an employee of the U.S. Consulate in Istanbul.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tuysuz|first1=Gul|last2=Koran|first2=Laura|title=Erdogan: Turkey does not recognize US ambassador after visa spat|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/10/10/politics/turkey-us-erdogan-us-ambassador/index.html|accessdate=July 6, 2018|publisher=CNN|date=October 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Cunningham|first1=Erin|last2=Fahim|first2=Kareen|title=U.S. and Turkey announce tit-for-tat travel restrictions, a sign of deteriorating alliance|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/us-halts-some-visa-services-in-turkey-citing-security-concerns/2017/10/08/02bdc01a-ac52-11e7-9b93-b97043e57a22_story.html|accessdate=July 6, 2018|publisher=Washington Post|date=October 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\nAfter the suspension of visa services in Turkey, Bass published a statement on [[YouTube]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7P9b3UarXho ''Ambassador John Bass's statement on the suspension of visa services in Turkey'' on YouTube]</ref>\n\nPresident [[Donald Trump]] named him as his choice to become the [[United States Ambassador to Afghanistan]] on July 20, 2017.<ref name=\"thehillbowdentrumptonominate\">{{cite news|last1=Bowden|first1=John|title=Trump to nominate Turkey envoy for ambassador to Afghanistan|url=http://thehill.com/homenews/administration/343056-trump-to-nominate-turkey-envoy-for-ambassador-to-afghanistan |accessdate=July 21, 2017|work=The Hill|date=July 20, 2017}}</ref> On September 28, 2017, his nomination was confirmed by the Senate.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lardner|first1=Richard|title=Senate confirms Huntsman as US ambassador to Russia |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/wireStory/senate-confirms-huntsman-us-ambassador-russia-50165267|accessdate=September 28, 2017 |work=ABC News|agency=Associated Press|language=en}}</ref> Bass left the position on January 6, 2020.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/06/us/politics/john-bass-afghanistan.html |title=John Bass, U.S. Envoy to Afghanistan, Steps Down on Cusp of New Peace Deal |last=Jakes |first=Lara |date=January 6, 2020 |work=The New York Times |access-date=January 6, 2020 |url-status=live |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Turkey\u2013United States relations]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://history.state.gov/departmenthistory/people/bass-john-r John R. Bass] at the [[Office of the Historian]]\n\n{{commons category}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-dip}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[John F. Tefft|John Tefft]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States Ambassador to Georgia]]|years=2009\u20132012}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Richard Norland]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Francis J. Ricciardone, Jr.|Francis Ricciardone]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States Ambassador to Turkey]]|years=2014\u20132017}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Philip Kosnett]]<br />(Charg\u00e9 d'Affaires a.i)}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[P. Michael McKinley]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States Ambassador to Afghanistan]]|years=2017\u20132020}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ross Wilson (ambassador)|Ross Wilson]]<br />(Charg\u00e9 d'Affaires)}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Stephen Mull]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Executive Secretariat|Executive Secretary of the Department of State]]|years=2012\u20132014}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Joseph Macmanus]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{US Ambassadors to Turkey}}\n{{US Ambassadors to Afghanistan}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bass, John R}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Ambassadors of the United States to Georgia (country)]]\n[[Category:Ambassadors of the United States to Turkey]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Syracuse University alumni]]\n[[Category:Trump administration personnel]]\n[[Category:Ambassadors of the United States to Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:United States Foreign Service personnel]]\n[[Category:21st-century American diplomats]]\n\n{{US-diplomat-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American diplomat and ambassador}}\n{{other people|John Bass}}\n{{Infobox Ambassador\n|name         = John Bass\n|image        = John R. Bass official photo.jpg\n|office       = [[United States Ambassador to Afghanistan]]\n|president    = [[Donald Trump]]\n|term_start   = December 12, 2017\n|term_end     = January 6, 2020\n|predecessor  = [[Hugo Llorens]]\n|successor    = [[Ross Wilson (ambassador)|Ross Wilson]] (acting)\n|office1      = [[United States Ambassador to Turkey]]\n|president1   = [[Barack Obama]]<br/>[[Donald Trump]]\n|term_start1  = October 20, 2014<ref name=\"Ambassador bio\">{{cite news|url=http://turkey.usembassy.gov/about-us/ambassador-john-bass.html|title=Ambassador Biography|publisher=Embassy of the United States Ankara, Turkey|accessdate=14 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129011614/http://turkey.usembassy.gov/about-us/ambassador-john-bass.html|archive-date=29 November 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|term_end1    = October 15, 2017<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://tr.usembassy.gov/embassy-consulates/ankara/former-ambassadors/ |title=Former Ambassadors |website=U.S. Embassy & Consulates in Turkey |language=en-US |access-date=2018-07-07}}</ref>\n|deputy1      = Philip Kosnett\n|predecessor1 = [[Francis J. Ricciardone Jr.]]\n|successor1   = [[David M. Satterfield]]\n|office2      = [[Executive Secretary of the Department of State]]\n|president2   = Barack Obama\n|term_start2  = October 8, 2012\n|term_end2    = July 18, 2014\n|predecessor2 = [[Stephen Mull]]\n|successor2   = [[Joseph Macmanus]]\n|office3      = [[Un