epartment Operations Center. He was sent to Iraq in 2008 as the leader of a provincial reconstruction team.<ref name=\"U.S. Ambassador to Turkey: Who Is John R. Bass?\"/> He speaks [[Italian language|Italian]] and [[French language|French]].<ref name=\"Ambassador bio\"/> \n\nIn October 2012, he was appointed [[Executive Secretary of the United States Department of State]] and served as the liaison between the State Department's many bureaus and the leadership offices of the [[Secretary of State|Secretary]], the Deputy Secretaries, and the [[Director of Policy Planning]].\n\nIn October 2017, after the U.S. decided to suspend non-immigrant visa services within Turkey, Turkish President [[Recep Tayyip Erdo\u011fan]] said the Turkish government would no longer recognize Bass's authority as a U.S. ambassador. The cancellation of visitor visas came after a Turkish court ordered the arrest of an employee of the U.S. Consulate in Istanbul.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tuysuz|first1=Gul|last2=Koran|first2=Laura|title=Erdogan: Turkey does not recognize US ambassador after visa spat|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/10/10/politics/turkey-us-erdogan-us-ambassador/index.html|accessdate=July 6, 2018|publisher=CNN|date=October 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Cunningham|first1=Erin|last2=Fahim|first2=Kareen|title=U.S. and Turkey announce tit-for-tat travel restrictions, a sign of deteriorating alliance|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/us-halts-some-visa-services-in-turkey-citing-security-concerns/2017/10/08/02bdc01a-ac52-11e7-9b93-b97043e57a22_story.html|accessdate=July 6, 2018|publisher=Washington Post|date=October 8, 2017}}</ref> \n\nAfter the suspension of visa services in Turkey, Bass published a statement on [[YouTube]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7P9b3UarXho ''Ambassador John Bass's statement on the suspension of visa services in Turkey'' on YouTube]</ref>\n\nPresident [[Donald Trump]] named him as his choice to become the [[United States Ambassador to Afghanistan]] on July 20, 2017.<ref name=\"thehillbowdentrumptonominate\">{{cite news|last1=Bowden|first1=John|title=Trump to nominate Turkey envoy for ambassador to Afghanistan|url=http://thehill.com/homenews/administration/343056-trump-to-nominate-turkey-envoy-for-ambassador-to-afghanistan |accessdate=July 21, 2017|work=The Hill|date=July 20, 2017}}</ref> On September 28, 2017, his nomination was confirmed by the Senate.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lardner|first1=Richard|title=Senate confirms Huntsman as US ambassador to Russia |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/wireStory/senate-confirms-huntsman-us-ambassador-russia-50165267|accessdate=September 28, 2017 |work=ABC News|agency=Associated Press|language=en}}</ref> Bass left the position on January 6, 2020.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/06/us/politics/john-bass-afghanistan.html |title=John Bass, U.S. Envoy to Afghanistan, Steps Down on Cusp of New Peace Deal |last=Jakes |first=Lara |date=January 6, 2020 |work=The New York Times |access-date=January 6, 2020 |url-status=live |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> \n\n==See also==\n*[[Turkey\u2013United States relations]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://history.state.gov/departmenthistory/people/bass-john-r John R. Bass] at the [[Office of the Historian]]\n\n{{commons category}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-dip}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[John F. Tefft|John Tefft]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States Ambassador to Georgia]]|years=2009\u20132012}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Richard Norland]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Francis J. Ricciardone, Jr.|Francis Ricciardone]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States Ambassador to Turkey]]|years=2014\u20132017}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Philip Kosnett]]<br/>(Charg\u00e9 d'Affaires a.i)}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[P. Michael McKinley]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States Ambassador to Afghanistan]]|years=2017\u20132020}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ross Wilson (ambassador)|Ross Wilson]]<br/>(Charg\u00e9 d'Affaires)}}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[St